cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper discusses a graph-based approach to modeling spherical data, which is commonly found in computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of graph neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses rotational symmetries, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
